{{Orphan|date=December 2015}}
'''Kienitz v. Sconnie Nation''', (7th Cir. 2014) is a copyright case in the [[United States Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit]], on the question of whether the use of a photograph by Michael Kienitz by printing and t-shirt company, Sconnie Nation LLC, was a [[copyright infringement]] or [[fair use]].<ref name=Standford-2014>{{Cite web|title = Kienitz v. Sconnie Nation, LLC|url =http://fairuse.stanford.edu/case/kienitz-v-sconnie-nation-llc/|website=[[Stanford University]] Copyright and Fair Use Center|accessdate=12 December 2015|date=15 September 2014}}</ref> The Seventh Circuit held in 2014 that Sconnie Nation's use was fair use,<ref name=USCopyrightOffice-Kienitz2014>{{Cite web|url=http://copyright.gov/fair-use/summaries/kienitz-sconnienation-7thcir2014.pdf|title=Kienitz v. Sconnie Nation, LLC, 766 F.3d 756 (7th Cir. 2014|work=[[U.S. Copyright Office]] Fair Use Index|date=2014|accessdate=12 December 2015}}</ref> applying the fair use statutory defense.<ref name=NatlLawReview-CircuitSplit-2015>{{cite news|title=A Circuit Split or Just a Surface-Blemish: Why Kienitz v. Sconnie Nation LLC Doesn’t Conflict with Cariou v. Prince|url=http://www.natlawreview.com/article/circuit-split-or-just-surface-blemish-why-kienitz-v-sconnie-nation-llc-doesn-t-confl|accessdate=12 December 2015|work=[[The National Law Review]]|date=17 February 2015}}</ref> While granting [[summary judgment]] to the defendants, the judgement notes that Kienitz did not present an argument for loss of commercial opportunity nor questioned why the defendants needed to use the specific photograph.<ref name=Kienitz-ApellateOpinion-2014>{{Cite web|title=Kienitz v. Sconnie Nation, LLC, No. 13-3004 (7th Cir. 2014)|url=http://law.justia.com/cases/federal/appellate-courts/ca7/13-3004/13-3004-2014-09-15.html|website=Justia Law|accessdate=12 December 2015}}</ref><ref name=MediaInstitute-CheshireCat-Part1-2014>{{cite news|last1=Smolla|first1=Prof. Rodney A.|title=Appropriation Art and the Smile of the Cheshire Cat|url=http://www.mediainstitute.org/IPI/2014/100614.php|accessdate=12 December 2015|work=The Media Institute|date=6 October 2014}}</ref><ref name=MediaInstitute-Kienitz-Part2-2015>{{cite news|last1=Smolla|first1=Prof. Rodney A.|title=Kienitz v. Sconnie Nation LLC, Part II|url=http://www.mediainstitute.org/IPI/2015/020415.php|accessdate=12 December 2015|work=The Media Institute|date=4 February 2015}}</ref><ref name=NYSBar-BlogPost-2014>{{cite web|last1=Werbin |first1=Barry |title=Kienitz v. Sconnie Nation LLC.- Seventh Circuit |url=http://nysbar.com/blogs/EASL/2014/09/kienitz_v_sconnie_nation_llc-_.html |website=The Entertainment, Arts and Sports Law Blog |accessdate=12 December 2015 |date=18 September 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222102812/http://nysbar.com/blogs/EASL/2014/09/kienitz_v_sconnie_nation_llc-_.html |archivedate=22 December 2015 |df= }}</ref>
